      <hedline>
        <hl1>Boorishness Knows No Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Remler letter responds to Peter Applebome's July 30 column on loud, obscene rap music being played by man at gas pump (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Thundering, profane rap music is as much an assault on personal space as is a recording of ''The Three Tenors'' coming from the neighbor's deck speakers when your own task is a nap in the hammock.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Thundering, profane rap music is as much an assault on personal space as is a recording of ''The Three Tenors'' coming from the neighbor's deck speakers when your own task is a nap in the hammock.</p>
        <p>''Please'' is essential for starting conversations in such circumstances. Once the request has been made, finish the conversation with ''Thank you.''</p>
        <p>ROBERT REMLER  Port Washington</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
